## Agent Configuration

### Batch Size
<!-- How many tasks /execute processes per batch (default: 2). -->
batch_size: 2

### Task Tracker
<!-- "file" (default), "github-issues", or "azure-boards".
     .claude/env.sh reads this line and exports TRACKER_BACKEND automatically.
     NB: "azure-boards" has all 12 verbs implemented in lib/tracker/tracker_azure.sh,
     but the surrounding bootstrap (init-azure-tracker script, AZ_* env vars in
     project.env, on-call agent Azure branch) is not yet shipped — only "file"
     and "github-issues" are bootstrappable end-to-end via init-project.sh. -->
tracker: file

### GitHub Project (if using github-issues mode)
<!-- Fill in BEFORE running the On-Call agent to initialise the repo.
     github_project_action: create | link | (blank to skip)
     github_project_name:   only needed when action is "create"
     github_project_number: only needed when action is "link" -->
github_project_action:
github_project_name:
github_project_number:

<!-- After On-Call runs (or you fill in .claude/project.env by hand), the
     resolved references go below: -->
<!-- project: [OWNER]/N -->
<!-- repo: [OWNER]/[REPO_NAME] -->

### Azure DevOps Project (if using azure-boards mode)
<!-- Fill in BEFORE running the On-Call agent. The org/project/repo must
     already exist in Azure DevOps — On-Call does not create them.
     azdo_org:       organization slug or URL (e.g. "myorg" or "https://dev.azure.com/myorg")
     azdo_project:   Azure DevOps project name (case-sensitive)
     azdo_repo:      Azure Repos repository name (case-sensitive)
     azdo_area_path: optional; defaults to azdo_project
     azdo_iteration_path: optional; leave blank for backlog
     azdo_work_item_type: optional; defaults to "Task" (Agile process). -->
azdo_org:
azdo_project:
azdo_repo:
azdo_area_path:
azdo_iteration_path:
azdo_work_item_type:

### Agent Variant
<!-- "github" for GitHub Issues, "azure" for Azure DevOps Boards, or
     "file" for file-based tracking. Must match the tracker: line above. -->
agent_variant: file

